        <item>
            <title>0.3.613</title>
            <pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 21:04:02 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>613</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>0.3.613</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h2>ChainLink 0.3.613</h2>
<p class="sub">Guided Bike Fit wizards, smarter coaching, an easier way to get your rides in, and polish.</p>

<h3>Getting your rides in — easier</h3>
<ul>
  <li>First-run setup now lets you <b>sign in to Garmin Connect</b> right there.</li>
  <li>The <b>Import</b> screen is reorganised by what works best: <b>connect a service once</b>
  (Garmin Connect, Ride with GPS, Karoo, Strava) at the top so your history and every new
  ride flow in; files and the USB cable in the middle; and the full Garmin account-export
  ZIP <b>last</b> — it's the slowest option (Garmin can take up to 30 days to email it),
  with a direct link to request it. Garmin Connect signs in right from that screen.</li>
</ul>

<h3>New: guided Bike Fit measurement</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>Measure step by step</b> — wizards for your body and each bike: one measurement per
  screen with a diagram and plain instructions, including a proper explanation of the
  <b>wall &amp; floor method</b> (the app does the subtraction).</li>
  <li>A green-amber-red <b>flexibility scale</b> shows how low your bars should go, your sweet
  spot, and where your current bike sits — with a "guide, not a fitter" note up top.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Smarter coaching &amp; a truer Power Profile</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>You rode — but not the plan</b>: each planned session compares prescribed vs actual,
  read in context, plus a weekly roll-up. Ask the coach to <b>adjust today's session</b> and
  it rewrites it; new <b>Critical Power</b> test and <b>.zwo / .fit workout import</b>.</li>
  <li>Rider type is now graded on <b>watts-per-kilo</b> (a light climber reads as a climber),
  and the <b>Coach's Read</b> compares your peaks against your current form instead of
  treating an old best as today's fitness.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Bikes, builds &amp; fixes</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>Compare builds</b> side by side and export a PDF; the <b>Workshop</b> tracks tools
  you've lent out.</li>
  <li><b>Back</b> returns you to the page you came from; tapping a ride title in Courses opens
  that ride; Rider Profile buttons and the expanded Courses view no longer misbehave on
  narrow layouts. The in-app manual has been thoroughly updated.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
